Question: Many universities require that freshman live on campus dorm during the first year of college. In your opinion, is this a good or a bad thing? Explain your opinion on this issue.
Answer:
Unless they have a great reason not to, all colleges should force freshmen to live on campus. This makes sense for two reasons. First, living on campus helps students adjust to college and feel like they have a home. Second, new students are less likely to know the area well enough to be able to find off-campus housing.